picsmedal came way back in 2008, when he clinched bronze in Beijing.\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 435, \"end\": 442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999977003426, \"rank\": 2.299671618058845e-09, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three years ago in Tokyo, Djokovic suffered defeat in the bronze medal match, just as he had done at London 2012.\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 464, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999780467541822, \"rank\": 2.193958376739204e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 471, \"end\": 479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.228232443544699e-20, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 546, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9972117798756559, \"rank\": 0.00279601590669334, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q13219666\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris Olympics 2024  While Djokovic beat Alcaraz in straight sets, in what was a repeat of the 2024 Wimbledon final, the Spaniard did not make it easy for the veteran Serbian, twice taking his rival to a tie break.\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.228232443544699e-20, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.591309281397404e-19, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 733, \"end\": 741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9023258584175194, \"rank\": 0.10821025617023404, \"text\": \"Spaniard\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 779, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9999912436266206, \"rank\": 8.747679715848476e-06, \"text\": \"Serbian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Djokovic summoned all of his experience and nous to finally get his hands on a gold medal - and the joy was clear to see as he sealed the victory in the French capital.\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 1000, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 985, \"end\": 991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8321316793740476, \"rank\": 0.19362101954941566, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After winning the decisive point, Djokovic dropped to his knees and put his head in his hands before looking to the heavens, with tears rolling down his face.\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1036, \"end\": 1044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.228232443544699e-20, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Najbolji teniser svih vremena.Najbolji sportista sveta.Sampion nad sampionima.Novak Djokovic \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b7\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b8\\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a4\\u008cSrbija uzima zlato na OI \\u00f0\\u009f\\u008f\\u0086Hvala kralju!pic.twitter.com/Eflk8Ky4sc  Moments later, the seven-time Wimbledon champion was pictured enjoying a touching moment with his daughter, Tara, as he joined his loved ones in the crowd inside Court Philippe Chatrier.\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1451, \"end\": 1455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tara_Maclay\", \"score\": 0.7893493004454105, \"rank\": 0.2668422156422753, \"text\": \"Tara\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tara_Maclay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tara_Maclay\"}, {\"begin\": 1505, \"end\": 1528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Court Philippe Chatrier\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the match, Tara\\u00a0was seen holding a sign which read, 'Dad is the best'.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tara_Maclay\", \"score\": 0.7893493004454105, \"rank\": 0.2668422156422753, \"text\": \"Tara\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tara_Maclay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tara_Maclay\"}, {\"begin\": 1591, \"end\": 1594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revenge\", \"score\": 0.9993611264127618, \"rank\": 0.0006392820068080423, \"text\": \"Dad\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revenge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revenge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It was an incredible battle, incredible fight.\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Honestly, when the last shot went through him, past him, that was the only moment I actually thought I could win the match,' Djokovic said after shortly after his victory.\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1783, \"end\": 1791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.228232443544699e-20, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I believed I could win but to actually win it\\u2026 he [Alcaraz] keeps on coming back, he keeps on asking me to play my best tennis.\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1883, \"end\": 1890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.591309281397404e-19, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I thought I started the first set well, I had chances, he had chances as well.\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 2040, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was probably fair to finish both sets with a tie break, to be honest.\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'We both had our chances to break but when it mattered we both came out with big serves, some big plays.\", \"from\": 2115, \"to\": 2219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not know what to say, I am still in shock.'\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2268, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked why the win was so special to him, Djokovic replied: 'It's everything but most of all it's my country.\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2311, \"end\": 2319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.228232443544699e-20, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Most of all it's the pride to play for Serbia.\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2420, \"end\": 2426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9999994487472278, \"rank\": 5.512265193135342e-07, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carlos, Rafa [Nadal], they love to play for Spain.\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2472, \"end\": 2477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999999998626663, \"rank\": 1.371823665553461e-09, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andy [Murray] loves to play for Great Britain, Roger [Federer] for Switzerland, Alex Zverev won in Tokyo for Germany.\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2511, \"end\": 2524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_Davis_Cup_team\", \"score\": 0.9995892668427208, \"rank\": 0.0004109010051621